cone mat or plastic wrap and place into the freezer to chill (approx. 1 hour)."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C."},{"content":"Once dough has chilled, roll out between silicone bread mat and a sheet of baking paper, or between two sheets of baking paper, to 0.5 cm thickness. Then, using a cooking cutter (5 cm), cut dough into approx. 45 rounds and place onto prepared baking trays."},{"content":"Bake for 8 minutes (180°C). Transfer biscuits onto a wire rack and allow to cool completely."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Mint layer"},{"content":"Place all mint layer ingredients into mixing bowl and blend <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then knead <b>30 sec\/<b>."},{"content":"Lightly dust silicone bread mat or work surface with extra icing sugar, then transfer dough onto it. Shape dough into a thin log (15 cm long, 2 cm wide). Wrap dough in baking paper and place into freezer for 1 hour. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Line 2 freezable containers or trays with baking paper, then spread cooled wafers out onto them."},{"content":"Remove mint thin dough from freezer and set aside for 2-3 minutes to soften slightly. Once softened, cut into slices (2 mm thick) and place 1 slice of the mint layer on top of each wafer. Transfer wafers back into freezable containers or onto trays, then place back into freezer for 30 minutes."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chocolate"},{"content":"Place chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add peppermint oil to taste, then melt for a further <b>3 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>, or until chocolate has fully melted. Transfer melted chocolate into a ceramic or glass bowl."},{"content":"Remove wafers from freezer, then working as quickly as possible so the chocolate doesn't harden, use 2 forks to gently dip each wafer into the chocolate."},{"content":"Place coated wafers back into containers or onto trays, then place into refrigerator for 2 hours to set."},{"content":"Serve immediately or transfer into a sealable container and place in refrigerator to store until ready to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<strong>After dinner mints<\/strong>: omit the wafer component of the recipe and reduce dark chocolate chips in step 13 to 350-400 g. Proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h 30m","45 pieces"]}